\f0\fs22 \cf0 Estrella is an open source and freely available radio-like client for ORF reflectors (e.g. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/chazapis/xlxd"}}{\fldrslt this fork}} of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/LX3JL/xlxd"}}{\fldrslt xlxd}}). It implements the D-STAR {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/chazapis/pydv#d-star-vocoder-extension"}}{\fldrslt vocoder extension}} that allows the use of the open source codec {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.rowetel.com/codec2.html"}}{\fldrslt Codec 2}} with D-STAR, so it establishes a DExtra connection directly to the reflector without the need of an AMBE chip. If the reflector has the appropriate hardware, it will transcode and bridge communications with "traditional" D-STAR transceivers (and in some cases also DMR and System Fusion).}